CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 14, 1951, pg. 24, reads: "JUNIORS OF HOMEWOOD - BRUSHTON UNIT, URBAN LEAGUE - The Juniors of the Homewood-Brushton Unit of the Urban League did so well at their bake sale to raise money for the Termon Avenue Children's Home that they held a party afterward. Left to right: President Joyce Boulden, Geraldine Griffie, vice president; Francine Walker, secretary; Geraldine Toler, corresponding secretary; Beverly Scott, assistant secretary; Muriel Henry, membership secretary, and Carole Vaughn, Fifia Hoskin, Janis Monroe, Myra Monroe, Ruthman Washington, Bob Scott, Patsy McGuire, Phyllis Owens, Sybol Owens, Mrs. Edythe V. Sandidge and Mrs. Doris Dyer, sponsor. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seventeen children of Juniors of Homewood-Brushton Unit of the Urban League,
